    "body": "You don't need to run a decompiler.  The needed data is in the trace.  Here's an example from our test vectors:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/hyperledger/besu/blob/b0de73fe57bfd8c398939b8e7edef577dd773e04/ethereum/api/src/test/resources/org/hyperledger/besu/ethereum/api/jsonrpc/trace/specs/trace-call/trace_call_0a_0_vmTrace.json#L23-L35\r\n\r\nThe `code` field that is peer to the `vmtrace` field has all the bytecode.  the `pc` field maps to the binary decoded fields.  If you want to keep it as hex then it is a simple `pc*2+2` transformation to get the text index.\r\n\r\nHowever the [EIP-3155 standard traces](https://eips.ethereum.org/EIPS/eip-3155) you get from `debug_traceTransaction` have the op field in-line.\r\n",
